A declarative agent for Microsoft 365 Agent Builder (Copilot Studio) that documents
DAX and M Code (Power Query) via two paths:

- **Path 1 — Copy-Paste**: User pastes code in, gets fully documented code back.
- **Path 2 — Semantic Model Scripts**: Agent generates ready-to-run scripts that
  apply documentation changes directly to a live Power BI semantic model via the
  XMLA endpoint. No manual copy-pasting of individual measures required.

Powered by GPT-5 or latest available OpenAI model in M365.

---

## 1. Manifest Fields

### Name
```
DAX & M Code Docs Agent
```

### Description
```
Documents DAX measures and M Code (Power Query) two ways: paste code to get
documented code back, or generate scripts to apply changes directly to your
semantic model via XMLA. Follows SQLBI standards for DAX and Microsoft metadata
conventions for M Code.
```

### Conversation Starters
```
1. Add a full docstring header to this DAX measure
2. Comment every step in this M Code query
3. Review my DAX naming conventions and suggest improvements
4. Add inline comments to explain the logic in this DAX formula
5. Document this custom M function with metadata records
6. Generate a Tabular Editor script to document all measures in my model
7. Generate a TMSL script to update my semantic model measures
8. Document all M Code queries in my semantic model via script
```

### Capabilities
- Enable **Code Interpreter** if available in your M365 plan
- Web search is NOT needed — all standards are embedded in the instructions
- For the full programmatic Path 2b (optional), register a custom REST API plugin
  — see Section 5 of this document for the implementation guide

