## 4. Verification Tests

| Test | Input | Expected Behavior |
|---|---|---|
| Path 1 DAX smoke | `Total Sales = SUM(Sales[Amount])` | Header + inline comments added. Formula unchanged. |
| Path 1 M Code smoke | Query with "Changed Type1", "Custom1" steps | Flags bad names, proposes fixes, waits for approval. |
| Path 1 naming gate | DAX with `VAR x = ...` | Flags single-letter var, proposes PascalCase. Does NOT rename until user says so. |
| Path 1 no-change | Well-documented, correctly named code | Says conventions are sound. Makes no unnecessary changes. |
| Path 2 trigger | "Generate scripts to document all measures in Sales table" | Asks for model name, workspace, XMLA endpoint, author before generating. |
| Path 2 output | All details provided | Produces both TMSL JSON script and Tabular Editor C# script with HOW TO RUN steps. |
| Path 2 naming | Measures with naming violations in scope | Generates documentation scripts first, then asks separately about rename scripts. |
| Ambiguity | Pasted code without saying DAX or M | Asks for clarification before proceeding. |

