## 5. Path 2 — Implementation Guide

### Option A: Script Generation Only (No Extra Infrastructure)

This is what the agent instructions above implement. The agent generates:
- **TMSL ALTER scripts** (JSON) — run in SSMS or Azure Data Studio against the XMLA endpoint
- **Tabular Editor C# scripts** — run in Tabular Editor 2 (free) or Tabular Editor 3

**No backend service, no Azure Function, no custom API plugin required.**
The user runs the scripts manually once. This covers 90% of use cases.

**Requirements for the user:**
- Power BI Premium capacity, Premium Per User (PPU), or Microsoft Fabric workspace
- XMLA read-write endpoint enabled (Workspace Settings → Premium → XMLA Endpoint → Read Write)
- SSMS, Azure Data Studio, or Tabular Editor installed

**TMSL ALTER script template (generated by agent):**
```json
{
  "alter": {
    "object": {
      "database": "SemanticModelName",
      "table": "TableName",
      "measure": "MeasureName"
    },
    "measure": {
      "name": "MeasureName",
      "expression": [
        "/* Measure: MeasureName */",
        "/* Author: Jane Smith */",
        "/* ... */",
        "VAR Result = SUM(Sales[Amount])",
        "RETURN Result"
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

**Tabular Editor C# script template (generated by agent):**
```csharp
// Document all measures in the Sales table
// Generated by DAX & M Code Docs Agent
// Run in Tabular Editor 2 or 3 (Model > C# Script)

foreach (var measure in Model.Tables["Sales"].Measures)
{
    // Wrap each measure expression with a docstring header
    string docstring = $@"/*
  Measure: {measure.Name}
  Author: Jane Smith
  Date Created: {DateTime.Now:yyyy-MM-dd}
  Last Modified: {DateTime.Now:yyyy-MM-dd}
  Version: 1.0

  Purpose: [Review and update this description]
  Business Context: [Review and update this]

  Dependencies:
    Tables:   [Review and update]
    Measures: [Review and update]
    Columns:  [Review and update]

  Return Value: Numeric value
  Notes: Auto-documented by DAX & M Code Docs Agent
*/
";
    // Prepend docstring only if one doesn't already exist
    if (!measure.Expression.TrimStart().StartsWith("/*"))
    {
        measure.Expression = docstring + measure.Expression;
    }
}

// Save all changes back to the semantic model via XMLA
Model.SaveChanges();

Info("Documentation applied to all measures in Sales table.");
```

